<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Showcase Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles",
  "telephone": "(323) 870-4790",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/showcase-refrigerator-repair/",
  "areaServed": [
    {"@type": "City", "name": "Los Angeles"},
    {"@type": "City", "name": "Beverly Hills"},
    {"@type": "City", "name": "Koreatown"},
    {"@type": "City", "name": "Monterey Park"},
    {"@type": "City", "name": "Pasadena"},
    {"@type": "City", "name": "Santa Monica"},
    {"@type": "City", "name": "West Hollywood"},
    {"@type": "City", "name": "Glendale"}
  ],
  "openingHoursSpecification": [
    {"@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification", "dayOfWeek": ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday","Sunday"], "opens": "07:00", "closes": "21:00"}
  ],
  "priceRange": "$$"
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does showcase refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our commercial diagnostic fee is $120, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most display case repairs run between $150 and $550. Anti-sweat heater replacement, door gasket, thermostat, evaporator fan motor, or condenser coil cleaning is toward the lower end. Compressor or refrigerant leak repair runs significantly higher. We provide a full written estimate before any work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why is my showcase refrigerator's glass fogging up?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Foggy or sweating glass on a display case is almost always an anti-sweat heater failure. Display cases use low-wattage electric heaters embedded in or around the door frame and glass to keep the glass surface slightly above the dew point — preventing condensation from forming on the outside of the cold glass. When the anti-sweat heater fails, ambient humidity condenses on the cold glass surface. This is a display case-specific failure that doesn't occur in standard reach-in refrigerators. Anti-sweat heater replacement is typically a $150–$280 repair."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My display case lighting is flickering or out — can you repair that?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Display case lighting — LED or fluorescent — is part of the presentation value of the case. Failed or flickering lighting directly affects how product looks to customers. We replace LED strips, fluorescent ballasts, and fixture assemblies in all major display case brands. For LED retrofit upgrades (replacing older fluorescent systems with LED), we can quote that alongside any repair."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My open-air display case is not holding temperature — what causes that in LA?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Open-air merchandisers in Los Angeles face a harder cooling challenge than in most US cities due to LA's warm ambient temperatures. The refrigeration system must maintain the product temperature against the open-air convective load — and in a warm store or outdoor market environment, this load is significantly higher. The most common cause of temperature failure in LA open-air cases is condenser coil fouling — dust and particulate accumulate faster in LA's climate and reduce heat rejection efficiency. Condenser cleaning restores performance in many cases before any parts need replacement."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Hussmann, True, Hill Phoenix, and Turbo Air display cases?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. True, Turbo Air, Hussmann, and Beverage-Air are the most common display case brands we service in Los Angeles retail and food service. Hill Phoenix and Structural Concepts are also common in larger grocery and specialty food operations. EPA 608 certified for all refrigerant work. Parts sourced through commercial refrigeration distributors same day for common brands."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How often should a showcase refrigerator be serviced?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every 6 months. A service visit includes condenser coil cleaning, anti-sweat heater function check, door gasket inspection, evaporator fan check, thermostat calibration, and refrigerant pressure verification. In LA's dusty environment, condenser cleaning intervals shorter than 6 months are appropriate for cases in high-foot-traffic areas or near kitchen equipment."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

