<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06 — Recent Repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What our technicians actually fixed recently</h2>

    <div class="repairs-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <div class="repair-title">Beverly Hills · Wine &amp; Cheese Shop · True GDM-49F Glass-Door Merchandiser</div>
        <h3>"Glass doors fogging up every morning — customers asking if the case is broken"</h3>
        <p>Anti-sweat heater failure on a True GDM-49F glass-door merchandiser in a Beverly Hills specialty cheese and charcuterie shop. The marine layer that rolls through Beverly Hills in the early mornings raises ambient humidity enough that when the anti-sweat heater fails, the cold glass doors fog immediately upon store opening. The owner had been wiping the doors manually each morning for two weeks before calling us.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Tested anti-sweat heater circuit — found open circuit on the door frame heater assembly, indicating heater wire failure. Replaced anti-sweat heater assembly with OEM True part. Verified door gasket seal on all three doors while on-site — found minor compression fatigue on center door bottom gasket, replaced as preventive measure. Tested through a full humidity cycle in the store. Both doors clear from first open. Case product visibility restored. Owner remarked that the shop had lost several cheese sales during the two weeks customers thought the case was broken.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-card">
        <div class="repair-title">Koreatown · Korean Market · Hussmann P5 Open-Air Merchandiser</div>
        <h3>"Produce case not holding temperature — top shelf items wilting by afternoon"</h3>
        <p>Failed evaporator fan motor on a Hussmann P5 open-air produce merchandiser in a Koreatown Korean market. Open-air cases have no door and rely on the evaporator fan to create a "curtain" of cold air across the open face of the case — without the fan, ambient warm air penetrates the case freely and the upper shelves warm rapidly. The lower shelves (closer to the evaporator) stayed cold while the upper shelves climbed to 50–55°F by early afternoon during a warm day.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Replaced evaporator fan motor with compatible Hussmann replacement. Cleaned evaporator coils which had moderate frost accumulation (indicating the defrost system had been marginally underperforming before the fan failure). Verified temperature uniformity across all shelves after repair — 36–38°F top to bottom. Checked and cleaned condenser coils — found significant dust accumulation from the market's high foot traffic environment. Enrolled market in 6-month maintenance contract. Open-air cases in busy market environments need condenser cleaning more frequently than manufacturer schedules designed for typical commercial settings.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-card">
        <div class="repair-title">Silver Lake · Artisan Bakery · Turbo Air TGM-72R Bakery Display Case</div>
        <h3>"Lighting flickering in the display case — pastries look terrible under the strobing light"</h3>
        <p>Failed LED driver in a Turbo Air TGM-72R bakery display case at a Silver Lake artisan bakery. The case had three LED light strips; the driver for the center strip had failed, causing that strip to flicker at approximately 2Hz — the most visually disruptive frequency. The bakery owner had been redirecting customers away from that section of the case while waiting for service. The pastry and croissant display was the first thing customers saw upon entering the shop.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Replaced failed LED driver. Inspected all three LED strips — found one strip with a partial segment failure (not visible during normal operation but confirmed during test). Replaced that strip as preventive measure while the case was already being serviced. Tested full lighting across all three strips through warm-up cycle. Also found during the visit that the door gasket on the right door had a small tear at the corner — replaced. Bakery owner commented that the display immediately looked significantly more inviting with consistent lighting restored. Discussed LED brightness upgrade for improved product display — provided quote for next scheduled service.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-card">
        <div class="repair-title">Monterey Park · Chinese Supermarket · Hill Phoenix E3 Multi-Deck Dairy Case</div>
        <h3>"Dairy case running warm — some items above 41°F, concerned about health inspection"</h3>
        <p>Dirty condenser coils and a partially blocked evaporator drain on a Hill Phoenix E3 multi-deck dairy case in a Monterey Park Chinese supermarket. The store had an LADPH inspection scheduled for the following week and the owner had noticed temperatures creeping into the 42–44°F range on the middle shelf. LA health code requires refrigerated display cases holding dairy, deli, and ready-to-eat products to maintain 41°F or below.</p>
        <div class="repair-detail">Deep-cleaned condenser coils — found 18 months of dust and grease accumulation from the store environment. Cleared partially blocked evaporator drain — standing water in the drain pan had partially frozen during overnight defrost, reducing effective drainage. After cleaning, verified temperatures across all shelves using calibrated probe: 37–39°F top to bottom, within LADPH compliance margins. Documented the service visit with pre-and-post temperature readings for the owner's health inspection records. Store passed inspection without issue. Enrolled in quarterly condenser cleaning — supermarket environments with high cooking activity nearby accumulate condenser fouling faster than retail-only stores.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

