<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Showcase refrigerator repair — what LA operators ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does showcase refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Diagnostic is $120, applied to repair if approved. Anti-sweat heater or door gasket runs $150–$280. Lighting repair runs $120–$300. Evaporator fan or condenser work runs $200–$450. Compressor or refrigerant work runs higher. Written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Why is my showcase refrigerator's glass fogging up?</h3>
        <p>Almost always anti-sweat heater failure — a low-wattage heater that keeps the glass surface above dew point. The refrigeration system may be fine. This is a display case-specific failure. Anti-sweat heater replacement is typically a same-day, $150–$280 repair. We carry parts for True, Turbo Air, and Beverage-Air on the van.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My display case lighting is out or flickering — can you fix it?</h3>
        <p>Yes. LED driver, LED strip, or fluorescent ballast replacement is a standard part of display case service. We also quote LED retrofit upgrades to replace older fluorescent systems with LED, which improves product presentation and reduces heat load inside the case.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My open-air case isn't holding temperature in warm weather — why?</h3>
        <p>Open-air cases in LA's warm ambient work harder than manufacturer specs designed for average US climates. The most common culprit is condenser coil fouling — dust accumulation reduces heat rejection and pushes the system past its cooling capacity on warm days. Condenser cleaning often restores performance before any parts replacement is needed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you provide LADPH documentation for temperature compliance?</h3>
        <p>Yes. We provide written service documentation including pre- and post-repair temperature readings for display cases holding LADPH-regulated products (dairy, deli, ready-to-eat). Useful for health inspections when you need to demonstrate corrective action.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Hussmann, True, Hill Phoenix, and Turbo Air display cases?</h3>
        <p>Yes. True, Turbo Air, Hussmann, and Beverage-Air are our most common LA display case service brands. Hill Phoenix and Structural Concepts also common in larger market operations. EPA 608 + C-38 certified for all refrigerant work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

